114struct RTCPReportBlock {
115 RTCPReportBlock()
116 : sender_ssrc(0),
117 source_ssrc(0),
118 fraction_lost(0),
119 packets_lost(0),
120 extended_highest_sequence_number(0),
121 jitter(0),
122 last_sender_report_timestamp(0),
123 delay_since_last_sender_report(0) {}
124
125 RTCPReportBlock(uint32_t sender_ssrc,
126 uint32_t source_ssrc,
127 uint8_t fraction_lost,
128 int32_t packets_lost,
129 uint32_t extended_highest_sequence_number,
130 uint32_t jitter,
131 uint32_t last_sender_report_timestamp,
132 uint32_t delay_since_last_sender_report)
133 : sender_ssrc(sender_ssrc),
134 source_ssrc(source_ssrc),
135 fraction_lost(fraction_lost),
136 packets_lost(packets_lost),
137 extended_highest_sequence_number(extended_highest_sequence_number),
138 jitter(jitter),
139 last_sender_report_timestamp(last_sender_report_timestamp),
140 delay_since_last_sender_report(delay_since_last_sender_report) {}
141
142 // Fields as described by RFC 3550 6.4.2.
143 uint32_t sender_ssrc; // SSRC of sender of this report.
144 uint32_t source_ssrc; // SSRC of the RTP packet sender.
145 uint8_t fraction_lost;
146 int32_t packets_lost; // 24 bits valid.
147 uint32_t extended_highest_sequence_number;
148 uint32_t jitter;
149 uint32_t last_sender_report_timestamp;
150 uint32_t delay_since_last_sender_report;
151};

214// NOTE! |kNumMediaTypes| must be kept in sync with RtpPacketMediaType!
215static constexpr size_t kNumMediaTypes = 5;
216enum class RtpPacketMediaType : size_t {
217 kAudio, // Audio media packets.
218 kVideo, // Video media packets.
219 kRetransmission, // Retransmisions, sent as response to NACK.
220 kForwardErrorCorrection, // FEC packets.
221 kPadding = kNumMediaTypes - 1, // RTX or plain padding sent to maintain BWE.
222 // Again, don't forget to udate |kNumMediaTypes| if you add another value!

298struct RtpPacketCounter {
299 RtpPacketCounter()
300 : header_bytes(0), payload_bytes(0), padding_bytes(0), packets(0) {}
301
302 explicit RtpPacketCounter(const RtpPacket& packet);
303
304 void Add(const RtpPacketCounter& other) {
305 header_bytes += other.header_bytes;
306 payload_bytes += other.payload_bytes;
307 padding_bytes += other.padding_bytes;
308 packets += other.packets;
309 }
310
311 void Subtract(const RtpPacketCounter& other) {
312 RTC_DCHECK_GE(header_bytes, other.header_bytes);
313 header_bytes -= other.header_bytes;
314 RTC_DCHECK_GE(payload_bytes, other.payload_bytes);
315 payload_bytes -= other.payload_bytes;
316 RTC_DCHECK_GE(padding_bytes, other.padding_bytes);
317 padding_bytes -= other.padding_bytes;
318 RTC_DCHECK_GE(packets, other.packets);
319 packets -= other.packets;
320 }
321
322 bool operator==(const RtpPacketCounter& other) const {
323 return header_bytes == other.header_bytes &&
324 payload_bytes == other.payload_bytes &&
325 padding_bytes == other.padding_bytes && packets == other.packets;
326 }
327
328 // Not inlined, since use of RtpPacket would result in circular includes.
329 void AddPacket(const RtpPacket& packet);
330
331 size_t TotalBytes() const {
332 return header_bytes + payload_bytes + padding_bytes;
333 }
334
335 size_t header_bytes; // Number of bytes used by RTP headers.
336 size_t payload_bytes; // Payload bytes, excluding RTP headers and padding.
337 size_t padding_bytes; // Number of padding bytes.
338 uint32_t packets; // Number of packets.
339};

341// Data usage statistics for a (rtp) stream.
342struct StreamDataCounters {
343 StreamDataCounters();
344
345 void Add(const StreamDataCounters& other) {
346 transmitted.Add(other.transmitted);
347 retransmitted.Add(other.retransmitted);
348 fec.Add(other.fec);
349 if (other.first_packet_time_ms != -1 &&
350 (other.first_packet_time_ms < first_packet_time_ms ||
351 first_packet_time_ms == -1)) {
352 // Use oldest time.
353 first_packet_time_ms = other.first_packet_time_ms;
354 }
355 }
356
357 void Subtract(const StreamDataCounters& other) {
358 transmitted.Subtract(other.transmitted);
359 retransmitted.Subtract(other.retransmitted);
360 fec.Subtract(other.fec);
361 if (other.first_packet_time_ms != -1 &&
362 (other.first_packet_time_ms > first_packet_time_ms ||
363 first_packet_time_ms == -1)) {
364 // Use youngest time.
365 first_packet_time_ms = other.first_packet_time_ms;
366 }
367 }
368
369 int64_t TimeSinceFirstPacketInMs(int64_t now_ms) const {
370 return (first_packet_time_ms == -1) ? -1 : (now_ms - first_packet_time_ms);
371 }
372
373 // Returns the number of bytes corresponding to the actual media payload (i.e.
374 // RTP headers, padding, retransmissions and fec packets are excluded).
375 // Note this function does not have meaning for an RTX stream.
376 size_t MediaPayloadBytes() const {
377 return transmitted.payload_bytes - retransmitted.payload_bytes -
378 fec.payload_bytes;
379 }
380
381 int64_t first_packet_time_ms; // Time when first packet is sent/received.
382 // The timestamp at which the last packet was received, i.e. the time of the
383 // local clock when it was received - not the RTP timestamp of that packet.
384 // https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-stats/#dom-rtcinboundrtpstreamstats-lastpacketreceivedtimestamp
385 absl::optional<int64_t> last_packet_received_timestamp_ms;
386 RtpPacketCounter transmitted; // Number of transmitted packets/bytes.
387 RtpPacketCounter retransmitted; // Number of retransmitted packets/bytes.
388 RtpPacketCounter fec; // Number of redundancy packets/bytes.
389};
390
391class RtpSendRates {
392 template <std::size_t... Is>
393 constexpr std::array<DataRate, sizeof...(Is)> make_zero_array(
394 std::index_sequence<Is...>) {
395 return {{(static_cast<void>(Is), DataRate::Zero())...}};
396 }
397
398 public:
399 RtpSendRates()
400 : send_rates_(
401 make_zero_array(std::make_index_sequence<kNumMediaTypes>())) {}
402 RtpSendRates(const RtpSendRates& rhs) = default;
403 RtpSendRates& operator=(const RtpSendRates&) = default;
404
405 DataRate& operator[](RtpPacketMediaType type) {
406 return send_rates_[static_cast<size_t>(type)];
407 }
408 const DataRate& operator[](RtpPacketMediaType type) const {
409 return send_rates_[static_cast<size_t>(type)];
410 }
411 DataRate Sum() const {
412 return absl::c_accumulate(send_rates_, DataRate::Zero());
413 }
414
415 private:
416 std::array<DataRate, kNumMediaTypes> send_rates_;
417};

428// Information exposed through the GetStats api.
429struct RtpReceiveStats {
430 // |packets_lost| and |jitter| are defined by RFC 3550, and exposed in the
431 // RTCReceivedRtpStreamStats dictionary, see
432 // https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-stats/#receivedrtpstats-dict*
433 int32_t packets_lost = 0;
434 uint32_t jitter = 0;
435
436 // Timestamp and counters exposed in RTCInboundRtpStreamStats, see
437 // https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-stats/#inboundrtpstats-dict*
438 absl::optional<int64_t> last_packet_received_timestamp_ms;
439 RtpPacketCounter packet_counter;
440};
